==Korean==

===Noun===
'''틀''' (teul, teur)
# [[frame]], [[framework]]
# [[model]], [[pattern]] 
# [[mould]], [[die]]
# [[device]], [[machine]]
# [[formalism]], [[formality]]

====Derived terms====
* [[문]]틀 (mun-) [[door]] frame 
* [[창]]틀 (chang-) [[window]] frame 
* 틀[[니]] (-ni, -li) [[artificial]] [[tooth]]
 
====Synonyms====
* [[테]] (te)

===Verb===
'''틀다''' (teulda)
# To [[turn]], [[twist]], [[wrench]]
# To [[thwart]]

====Derived terms====
* [[비틀다]] (biteulda) To [[twist]], [[wrench]]
* [[틀]]어막다 (teulEo-, teurEo-) To [[stuff]], [[stop up]] (a hollow, mouth, ear, etc., literally, "by turning" something forcibly into it.) 

====Related terms====
* [[도르다]] (doreuda) To [[deceive]]; [[shift]]; [[vomit]]
* [[돌다]] (dolda) (intransitive) To [[turn]], [[revolve]]
* [[돌리다]] (dollida) (transitive) To [[rotate]], [[spin]], [[turn]]; [[attribute]]; (intransitive) to be [[deceived]]
* [[틀리다]] (teullida) To be [[turned]]; [[different]], [[mistaken]], [[wrong]]

